## When to create a new spec type

Create a new spec type when a distinct layer, concern, or artifact in the system needs a repeatable documentation contract. A good spec type:

- Documents **one specific kind of artifact** (a table, an endpoint, a consumer ŌĆö not a mix)
- Has a **fixed set of sections** that apply consistently across all documents of that type
- Produces documents that **live under a single `specs/` sub-path**
- Can be illustrated with **at least one real example** from the codebase

Do not create a new spec type for a one-off document. Use it only when two or more documents of the same shape already exist or are planned.

